column29: "Have not considered" above is not strictly correct - I have considered all the above but decided against them all.  The one think I am looking into is installing a system to divert excess solar (i.e. the amount that is currently exported) to the hot water tank and resistive heating, so as to minimise solar export.
column57: I have looked into battery purchase and decided against it.  Reasons: Currently battery systems are not economically viable (guaranteed service life is less than payback period); no end-of-life Li-ion battery recycling exists; there is a net environmental detriment to using batteries in Tasmania as the energy to make batteries could be avoided if excess solar is exported and the hydro energy is stored (i.e. energy stored as water in dams).
